{"info": {"author": "DCsunset", "author_email": "DCsunset@protonmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Environment :: Console", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Terminals"], "description": "# powerline-cpu-temp\n\n`powerline-cpu-temp` is a Powerline segment to show CPU temperature.\n\n## Installation\n\nUsing pip:\n\n```\npip3 install powerline-cpu-temp\n```\n\nOr clone this repository and run:\n\n```\npython3 setup.py install\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nFirst, it is required to add `cpu_temp` and `cpu_temp_gradient` highlight groups in the colorscheme configurations:\n(You can easily customize the color scheme by changing the highlight group settings.)\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"cpu_temp\": { \"fg\": \"gray8\", \"bg\": \"gray0\", \"attrs\": [] },\n\t\"cpu_temp_gradient\": { \"fg\": \"green_yellow_orange_red\", \"bg\": \"gray0\", \"attrs\": [] }\n}\n```\n\nThen add the following settings to the Powerline configuration file:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"function\": \"powerline_cpu_temp.cpu_temp\"\n}\n```\n\nYou can specify the arguments:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"function\": \"powerline_cpu_temp.cpu_temp\",\n\t\"args\": {\n\t\t\"format\": \"{value:.0f}\u00b0C\",\n\t\t\"threshold_good\": 50,\n\t\t\"threshold_bad\": 90\n\t}\n}\n```\n\nAvailable arguments:\n\n* `format`(`string`): format string, receives `value` as an argument\n\n* `threshold_good` (`float`): threshold for gradient level 0:\ntemperature below this value will have this gradient level.\n\n* `threshold_bad` (`float`): threshold for gradient level 100:\ntemperature above this value will have this gradient level.\nTemperature between `threshold_good` and `threshold_bad` receive gradient level that indicates relative position in this interval:\n(`100 * (cur-good) / (bad-good)`).\n\n## Dependencies\n\n* [psutil](https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil)\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/DCsunset/powerline-cpu-temp", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "powerline-cpu-temp", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/powerline-cpu-temp/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/powerline-cpu-temp/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/DCsunset/powerline-cpu-temp"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/powerline-cpu-temp/0.1.0/", "requires_dist": ["psutil"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "A Powerline segment to show CPU temperature", "version": "0.1.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>powerline-cpu-temp</h1>\n<p><code>powerline-cpu-temp</code> is a Powerline segment to show CPU temperature.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Using pip:</p>\n<pre><code>pip3 install powerline-cpu-temp\n</code></pre>\n<p>Or clone this repository and run:</p>\n<pre><code>python3 setup.py install\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>First, it is required to add <code>cpu_temp</code> and <code>cpu_temp_gradient</code> highlight groups in the colorscheme configurations:\n(You can easily customize the color scheme by changing the highlight group settings.)</p>\n<pre><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n\t<span class=\"nt\">\"cpu_temp\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"nt\">\"fg\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"gray8\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nt\">\"bg\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"gray0\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nt\">\"attrs\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">[]</span> <span class=\"p\">},</span>\n\t<span class=\"nt\">\"cpu_temp_gradient\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"nt\">\"fg\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"green_yellow_orange_red\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nt\">\"bg\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"gray0\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nt\">\"attrs\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">[]</span> <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Then add the following settings to the Powerline configuration file:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n\t<span class=\"nt\">\"function\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"powerline_cpu_temp.cpu_temp\"</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre>\n<p>You can specify the arguments:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n\t<span class=\"nt\">\"function\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"powerline_cpu_temp.cpu_temp\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n\t<span class=\"nt\">\"args\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"nt\">\"format\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"{value:.0f}\u00b0C\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"nt\">\"threshold_good\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"nt\">\"threshold_bad\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">90</span>\n\t<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Available arguments:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><code>format</code>(<code>string</code>): format string, receives <code>value</code> as an argument</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><code>threshold_good</code> (<code>float</code>): threshold for gradient level 0:\ntemperature below this value will have this gradient level.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><code>threshold_bad</code> (<code>float</code>): threshold for gradient level 100:\ntemperature above this value will have this gradient level.\nTemperature between <code>threshold_good</code> and <code>threshold_bad</code> receive gradient level that indicates relative position in this interval:\n(<code>100 * (cur-good) / (bad-good)</code>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Dependencies</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil\" rel=\"nofollow\">psutil</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6746453, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "485920270d259734563500e2fcadbe3f", "sha256": "5858e492d7c8b594b75cb656e7c0eef57486ea07683f7c1a73deb683385cb67b"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "powerline_cpu_temp-0.1.0-py3.7.egg", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "485920270d259734563500e2fcadbe3f", "packagetype": "bdist_egg", "python_version": "3.7", "requires_python": null, "size": 2934, "upload_time": "2020-03-04T09:20:02", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-04T09:20:02.519685Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/ae/1d/0ee8579577146daa8b6830d9b0b15e2fa3d3f7c543a088125a671f67306a/powerline_cpu_temp-0.1.0-py3.7.egg", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "e1f044b4e7a4adc888be0f634f02ad72", "sha256": "6fb7fe64872fb0af750539b483f99c4a90a4ed0ac9b0f6e2b70b02c90363ee4b"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "powerline_cpu_temp-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "e1f044b4e7a4adc888be0f634f02ad72", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 3428, "upload_time": "2020-03-04T09:19:57", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-04T09:19:57.653306Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/e9/76/fdf953ca132052925ece4198bbb7cd1491cfff6eda1a0d533b3e72ccb824/powerline_cpu_temp-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "f9a83e0b974a02285365763febd63c91", "sha256": "f44b1b885eb360d3d8e135ab48112e63d3da18ba41d901f6ed7a16843bc9b698"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "powerline-cpu-temp-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "f9a83e0b974a02285365763febd63c91", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2278, "upload_time": "2020-03-04T09:20:00", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-04T09:20:00.171270Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.o